tel 1.0 https://tel-lang.org/schema/tel-schema

# A small schema demonstrating struct validators (§21.6 of the TEL
# Specification). The `event` record carries a struct-level validator
# `start-precedes-end` that examines the `start-date` and `end-date`
# fields together — a cross-field rule that no scalar validator could
# express alone.
#
# A parser configured with this schema MUST be supplied (via the
# validator callback) with an implementation of `start-precedes-end`
# that:
#
#   - receives a `ValidationRequest::Struct` with `method =
#     "start-precedes-end"` and an `element: StructView` whose
#     `compound` is the `event` body;
#   - reads `start-date` and `end-date` as scalar children;
#   - returns `Valid` if start-date ≤ end-date in lexicographic order
#     (ISO 8601 dates compare correctly this way), or
#   - returns `Invalid(Diagnostic::Struct { message, fields })` where
#     `fields` may contain a nested `Diagnostic::Scalar` pinpointing
#     `end-date` as the offending field.
#
# See `demo/struct-validator-document.tel` for a document that
# triggers the failure path, and `tests::struct_validator_worked_example`
# in `src/lib.rs` for a runnable example.

name event-log

record event
  field title string
  field start-date string
  field end-date string
  validate start-precedes-end

document
  field event optional repeatable event
